On Sat, 9 Mar 2002, Westfalia wrote:

> If he's going to learn to weld, why not do it right and learn to make nice
> butt welds.  No chance of that seam collecting dirt/water/gunk and starting
> the rotting process all over again.  Take the time to trim and fit
> correctly.  Just my opinion

Agreed! That's what I did, and none of it has failed in 27 years. When I
had the whole resto 20 years later, the resto-shop guys saw the work and
commented approvingly. And there was no rust at the weld bead.

